video.title: Seinfeld
video.synopsis: The "show about nothing" is a sitcom landmark, with comic Jerry and his three sardonic friends finding laughs in both the mundane and the ridiculous.

episodes.synopsis: A woman Jerry met in Michigan flies into New York and asks to stay with him, but he's unsure if it's intended to be a romantic situation.
episodes.title: Seinfeld

episodes.synopsis: After recently breaking up with Elaine, Jerry meets a woman at a party but only learns where she works, leading him to stake out her office.
episodes.title: The Stake Out

episodes.synopsis: Jerry’s apartment gets robbed, leading him to want to move to a different place and give his current apartment to Elaine.
episodes.title: The Robbery

episodes.synopsis: Jerry attempts to "break up" with an old childhood friend who annoys him. George worries his girlfriend will leave him over dental floss.
episodes.title: Male Unbonding

episodes.synopsis: George convinces Jerry to invest in a stock. Jerry's weekend in Vermont with a woman doesn't go as planned. Elaine is allergic to her boyfriend's cats.
episodes.title: The Stock Tip

episodes.synopsis: After George breaks up with a woman he finds annoying, Jerry dates her and also finds her grating, yet he can’t bring himself to end the relationship.
episodes.title: The Ex-Girlfriend

episodes.synopsis: When Jerry’s parents visit New York, Jerry upsets a family member with a remark about ponies. Kramer wants to build "levels" in his apartment.
episodes.title: The Pony Remark

episodes.synopsis: Jerry buys an expensive suede jacket with an odd lining. Jerry and George get stuck alone with Elaine's intimidating father.
episodes.title: The Jacket

episodes.synopsis: George goes to great lengths to prevent a woman he's dating from hearing an answering machine message. Jerry's date likes a commercial he hates.
episodes.title: The Phone Message

episodes.synopsis: Jerry tells Elaine about an open apartment in his building, but soon regrets it. George wears a wedding ring to attract women.
episodes.title: The Apartment

episodes.synopsis: Jerry is convinced that a house cleaner stole a statue from his apartment, threatening Elaine's deal with a client.
episodes.title: The Statue

episodes.synopsis: George seeks revenge on his boss after he quits and then tries to get his job back. Jerry and Kramer think a laundromat owner stole money from Jerry.
episodes.title: The Revenge

episodes.synopsis: Jerry tries to decipher an unintelligible note he wrote in the middle of the night. George visits a holistic healer to deal with a medical issue.
episodes.title: The Heart Attack

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and Elaine attempt to resume a sexual relationship — with strict rules. But Elaine's birthday might ruin the arrangement.
episodes.title: The Deal

episodes.synopsis: Elaine hosts a friend's baby shower at Jerry's apartment, where George hopes to confront a former date. Kramer convinces Jerry to get illegal cable.
episodes.title: The Baby Shower

episodes.synopsis: Jerry, Elaine and George wait — for what seems like forever — for a table at a Chinese restaurant, after being told it would be “five or 10 minutes.”
episodes.title: The Chinese Restaurant

episodes.synopsis: Elaine and George fear they inadvertently got a busboy fired. Elaine realizes she can't stand a boyfriend who came from out of town to stay with her.
episodes.title: The Busboy

episodes.synopsis: Jerry scares a massage therapist, while George questions his sexuality after a massage. Kramer insists he saw Joe DiMaggio at a donut shop.
episodes.title: The Note

episodes.synopsis: George breaks up with his girlfriend, who happens to be in the middle of helping Jerry with a tax audit. Kramer dates Elaine’s roommate.
episodes.title: The Truth

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and Elaine visit Florida for a ceremony honoring Jerry's dad. Jack Klompus gives Jerry a pen. Elaine hurts her back on an uncomfortable bed.
episodes.title: The Pen

episodes.synopsis: A drunk airplane passenger asks Jerry to look after his dog. George and Elaine find it awkward to hang out alone without Jerry.
episodes.title: The Dog

episodes.synopsis: A stern library investigator goes after Jerry for an overdue book. George thinks a homeless man is a former teacher who tortured him in high school.
episodes.title: The Library

episodes.synopsis: The four lose their car in a parking garage, imperiling Elaine's new goldfish, George's night out with his parents and Jerry's painfully full bladder.
episodes.title: The Parking Garage

episodes.synopsis: Jerry befriends the owner of a Pakistani café and convinces him to make some changes. George's girlfriend asks him to take an IQ test.
episodes.title: The Cafe

episodes.synopsis: Elaine anonymously records a racy voiceover for Jerry as a joke, causing George to become attracted to her. George orders baldness cream from China.
episodes.title: The Tape

episodes.synopsis: George's girlfriend gets plastic surgery. Jerry dates a woman he finds sexy but dislikes spending time with. Kramer wants a very specific jacket.
episodes.title: The Nose Job

episodes.synopsis: George, Elaine and Jerry get stranded at a party on Long Island. The host later shows up unannounced at Jerry’s apartment.
episodes.title: The Stranded

episodes.synopsis: George gets a gig parking cars. Kramer lands a role in a Woody Allen movie. Jerry has an unpleasant rental car experience. Elaine dates a much older man.
episodes.title: The Alternate Side

episodes.synopsis: George buys a cashmere sweater — with a small flaw — for Elaine. George has a sexual encounter at work. Elaine's boyfriend falls off the wagon.
episodes.title: The Red Dot

episodes.synopsis: During separate subway rides, Jerry befriends a nude man, George meets a woman, Kramer gets a horse-racing tip and Elaine tries to get to a wedding.
episodes.title: The Subway

episodes.synopsis: A Pez dispenser causes George's girlfriend to flub a piano recital. Kramer creates a cologne that smells like the beach. Jerry hosts an intervention.
episodes.title: The Pez Dispenser

episodes.synopsis: Jerry gets close to a woman whose boyfriend tried to kill himself. George gets a mysterious warning from a psychic. Elaine fasts for a medical procedure.
episodes.title: The Suicide

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and Elaine fix George up with Elaine's friend, Cynthia, and soon after their first date, George learns that Cynthia may be pregnant.
episodes.title: The Fix-Up

episodes.synopsis: Jerry befriends baseball star Keith Hernandez, who takes an interest in Elaine. George concocts an unemployment scheme involving "Vandelay Industries."
episodes.title: The Boy Friend, Part I & II

episodes.synopsis: Stranded at the airport, Jerry and George decide George should impersonate a man named "O’Brien" to get a ride in a limo back to the city.
episodes.title: The Limo

episodes.synopsis: Jerry dates a hit-and-run driver. George is offended by people who don’t say, "God bless you" after a sneeze. Mary Hart's voice causes issues for Kramer.
episodes.title: The Good Samaritan

episodes.synopsis: Jerry dates an artist who paints a portrait of Kramer. George feels obligated to buy art. Elaine wears a Baltimore cap to a Yankees game.
episodes.title: The Letter

episodes.synopsis: Kramer's friend, Mike, calls Jerry a "phony." George and Mike fight over a parallel parking spot. Jerry inadvertently breaks some bad news to a child.
episodes.title: The Parking Space

episodes.synopsis: Jerry asks for his spare keys back from Kramer, who then moves to California. George and Jerry discover Elaine wrote a script for "Murphy Brown."
episodes.title: The Keys

episodes.synopsis: George and Jerry go to LA for Jerry to appear on the “Tonight Show.” Kramer struggles to land acting roles. George annoys George Wendt and Corbin Bernsen.
episodes.title: The Trip, Part I

episodes.synopsis: After Kramer is detained in LA as a suspect in a string of murders, George and Jerry try to clear Kramer’s name and reunite with their friend.
episodes.title: The Trip, Part II

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and George develop a sitcom pitch for NBC, and George dates a network executive. Kramer is kicked in the head. Newman gets a speeding ticket.
episodes.title: The Pitch/Ticket

episodes.synopsis: Morty claims a doctor stole his wallet. Elaine attempts to break up with her psychiatrist boyfriend. George negotiates the pilot deal with NBC.
episodes.title: The Wallet

episodes.synopsis: Jerry tries to buy his old watch back from Uncle Leo. George makes a desperate plea to Russell Dalrymple. Kramer poses as Elaine’s boyfriend.
episodes.title: The Watch

episodes.synopsis: Jerry, George, Elaine and Susan visit a boy who lives in a plastic bubble. George and the boy argue over Trivial Pursuit. Jerry regrets an autograph.
episodes.title: The Bubble Boy

episodes.synopsis: Susan learns an uncomfortable truth about her father after telling him about the cabin. Jerry's dirty talk offends his date. Kramer seeks Cuban cigars.
episodes.title: The Cheever Letters

episodes.synopsis: George and Kramer try to sell extra tickets to "Pagliacci" on the street. Elaine and Jerry discover their separate connections to Joe Davola.
episodes.title: The Opera

episodes.synopsis: Jerry’s new girlfriend is a virgin. Jerry pitches George's off-the-cuff "butler" storyline to NBC. Elaine causes Ping to have an accident.
episodes.title: The Virgin

episodes.synopsis: George's mother catches him in a compromising position, leading the four to wager over who can be "master of their domain" for the longest.
episodes.title: The Contest

episodes.synopsis: Jerry takes a first-class seat on a flight, leaving Elaine to suffer in coach. George and Kramer rush from JFK to LaGuardia to pick them up.
episodes.title: The Airport

episodes.synopsis: Elaine mails out a revealing Christmas card. Jerry’s date thinks she sees him picking his nose. George visits a therapist. Kramer confronts Calvin Klein.
episodes.title: The Pick

episodes.synopsis: The gang agrees to meet for a movie. Jerry gets stuck in a taxi with a comic he doesn't like. George battles with a theater usher.
episodes.title: The Movie

episodes.synopsis: George dates a lawyer who's representing Ping in a lawsuit against Elaine. Babu gets detained by INS due to a mail mixup. Kramer punches Mickey Mantle.
episodes.title: The Visa

episodes.synopsis: Elaine battles with a chef over a pair of shoes. Jerry and George visit an ill Russell and get caught leering at his daughter.
episodes.title: The Shoes

episodes.synopsis: A student newspaper reporter mistakenly portrays George and Jerry as a couple, leading them to conflicted emotions about being perceived as gay.
episodes.title: The Outing

episodes.synopsis: Elaine, Jerry and George volunteer with senior citizens. Kramer and Newman try to sell an older man's record collection. A woman's goiter shocks Elaine.
episodes.title: The Old Man

episodes.synopsis: Elaine thinks Jerry’s girlfriend has breast implants. George tries to get a bereavement discount on airfare, and is accused of double-dipping a chip.
episodes.title: The Implant

episodes.synopsis: Jerry can't remember his girlfriend's name, only that it rhymes with a female body part. Kramer and Jerry observe a surgery. George buys expensive art.
episodes.title: The Junior Mint

episodes.synopsis: An overwhelming odor takes hold in Jerry's car, and he can’t get it out. George learns that Susan is dating a woman, who becomes attracted to Kramer.
episodes.title: The Smelly Car

episodes.synopsis: Kramer convinces George to make an unfortunate parking decision. Kramer dates a wheelchair user. The gang buys a TV for a couple that breaks up.
episodes.title: The Handicap Spot

episodes.synopsis: George and Jerry finally produce their sitcom pilot. George is bothered by a spot on his lip. Elaine thinks Monk's only hires large-breasted servers.
episodes.title: The Pilot, Part I & II

episodes.synopsis: George struggles to satisfy his new girlfriend. Elaine admits to "faking it" with Jerry in the past. Kramer gets banned from a fruit stand.
episodes.title: The Mango

episodes.synopsis: Kramer dates a "low talker," leading to an embarrassing fashion moment for Jerry on TV. George gets noticed for his "exquisite" hands.
episodes.title: The Puffy Shirt

episodes.synopsis: George creates a fiasco involving a sugar-addicted optometrist, ladies' eyeglasses and Jerry's girlfriend. Elaine thinks a dog bite gives her rabies.
episodes.title: The Glasses

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and Kramer think their accountant is on drugs. Elaine fights with her boyfriend about punctuation. George interviews to be a bra salesman.
episodes.title: The Sniffing Accountant

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and Elaine arrange an ill-fated circumcision ceremony. George's good parking spot at a hospital gets ruined. Kramer sees a "pig man."
episodes.title: The Bris

episodes.synopsis: George gets caught on TV eating a messy sundae. Jerry dates a deaf tennis official. Kramer auditions to be a "ball man." Elaine fakes hearing loss.
episodes.title: The Lip Reader

episodes.synopsis: The gang gets suspicious of a supposed “non-fat” frozen yogurt shop. Elaine dates George's nemesis, Lloyd Braun. Jerry curses in front of a kid.
episodes.title: The Non-Fat Yogurt

episodes.synopsis: George starts a new job he knows nothing about and may never have even been offered. Jerry tries to switch barbers. Elaine hosts a bachelor auction.
episodes.title: The Barber

episodes.synopsis: Elaine dates a man who shares his name with a serial killer. George becomes oddly drawn to Jerry’s masseuse girlfriend, who refuses to massage Jerry.
episodes.title: The Masseuse

episodes.synopsis: Jerry gives Elaine an offensive gift. Frank gets mad at Elaine over a "TV Guide." Kramer pitches a book about coffee tables. George gets grounded.
episodes.title: The Cigar Store Indian

episodes.synopsis: George wants to convert to Latvian Orthodox. A sister at the church finds Kramer irresistible. Jerry discovers fungicide in his girlfriend’s apartment.
episodes.title: The Conversion

episodes.synopsis: A woman withholds toilet paper from Elaine. George becomes enamored with Elaine's "cool guy" boyfriend. Kramer keeps calling a phone sex line.
episodes.title: The Stall

episodes.synopsis: George and Kramer (and George's jacket) cause havoc at a wine shop. A babka and a black-and-white cookie spell trouble for Jerry and Elaine at a bakery.
episodes.title: The Dinner Party

episodes.synopsis: Jerry tells George's ex-crush that George is now a marine biologist. Elaine has a run-in with a Russian author. Kramer hits golf balls into the ocean.
episodes.title: The Marine Biologist

episodes.synopsis: Jerry’s girlfriend’s father, Poppie, is "a little sloppy." Kramer notices a mannequin looks just like Elaine. George buys a suit that "swooshes."
episodes.title: The Pie

episodes.synopsis: Kramer gives questionable advice to his friend, Mickey. Jerry tries to cheer up his hospitalized friend. Elaine dates a man who "took it out."
episodes.title: The Stand-In

episodes.synopsis: Jerry's girlfriend poses as his wife for a dry cleaning discount. Elaine gets mixed signals from a guy at the gym. George pees in the shower.
episodes.title: The Wife

episodes.synopsis: Elaine dates a "close talker." George sells Frank’s old clothes. Kramer and Morty try to sell raincoats. Jerry and his girlfriend see "Schindler's List."
episodes.title: The Raincoats, Part I & II

episodes.synopsis: George struggles to keep his cool in a fire. Elaine's co-worker heckles Jerry’s act, and Jerry's retaliation causes an accident.
episodes.title: The Fire

episodes.synopsis: The gang visits a friend's new baby in the Hamptons. George's girlfriend goes topless. A doctor's wording puzzles Elaine. George experiences "shrinkage."
episodes.title: The Hamptons

episodes.synopsis: George does the opposite of everything his instincts say. Jerry is "Even Steven." Kramer promotes his coffee table book. Elaine falls on hard times.
episodes.title: The Opposite

episodes.synopsis: Jerry dates a Miss America contestant — with Kramer as a self-appointed chaperone. George proposes new Yankees uniforms. Elaine gets a new job.
episodes.title: The Chaperone

episodes.synopsis: George seeks credit for buying a salad. Elaine searches for a rare pencil. Jerry dates a woman who dated Newman. Kramer's golf game leads to trouble.
episodes.title: The Big Salad

episodes.synopsis: Jerry volunteers for a PBS pledge drive. A "high talker" confounds Elaine. Jerry cashes old checks from his Nana. Mr. Pitt eats a candy bar strangely.
episodes.title: The Pledge Drive

episodes.synopsis: Jerry dates a woman with a confusing last name who offers advice to Estelle. Kramer switches to boxer shorts. Frank's lawyer wears a cape.
episodes.title: The Chinese Woman

episodes.synopsis: George cuts corners on a book club assignment. Kramer and Poppie start a pizza business. Jerry’s couch gets defiled. Elaine's personal views are tested.
episodes.title: The Couch

episodes.synopsis: Jerry dates a gymnast. Mr. Pitt becomes obsessed with a 3D image. George eats "trash" and reveals an odd bathroom habit. Kramer gets a kidney stone.
episodes.title: The Gymnast

episodes.synopsis: Jerry bickers with Bania over what constitutes a "meal." Elaine's English visitor overstays his welcome. George has an awkward date with a waitress.
episodes.title: The Soup

episodes.synopsis: Kramer takes all of Jerry’s shoes to get cleaned. George brags about buying Jon Voight’s car. The gang goes to Tim Whatley’s Thanksgiving party.
episodes.title: The Mom & Pop Store

episodes.synopsis: George gets too close to his new assistant. Jerry uses unethical dry cleaners. Elaine and Kramer have an adventure at Barneys.
episodes.title: The Secretary

episodes.synopsis: An old rival accuses Jerry of cheating in a race years ago. Elaine dates a communist and gets banned by a restaurant. Kramer becomes a mall Santa.
episodes.title: The Race

episodes.synopsis: Jerry wants to break up with a woman to date her roommate. George thinks his girlfriend has an eating disorder. Kramer’s first name is revealed.
episodes.title: The Switch

episodes.synopsis: Whatley "regifts" a label maker to thank Jerry for Super Bowl tickets. Kramer and Newman play Risk. George's girlfriend's roommate looks just like him.
episodes.title: The Label Maker

episodes.synopsis: A friend lies to Jerry and George about having cancer. Elaine tries to get back at an ex-boyfriend. Kramer helps track down a parking “scofflaw.”
episodes.title: The Scofflaw

episodes.synopsis: This highlight show looks back at the funniest moments from the first 99 episodes of the series.
episodes.title: 100th Episode Special

episodes.synopsis: Elaine falls for a gay man. Jerry tries to prove that he doesn't watch "Melrose Place." George dates a bald woman. Kramer gets paid to be in police lineups.
episodes.title: The Beard

episodes.synopsis: George is angered by a cancellation policy. Kramer's idea to make their building more friendly irks Jerry. Morty and Uncle Leo fight over $50.
episodes.title: The Kiss Hello

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and Elaine have run-ins with the doorman at Mr. Pitt's building. Frank and Kramer develop a new undergarment for men.
episodes.title: The Doorman

episodes.synopsis: A mutual acquaintance refers to himself strangely. Jerry get suspicious of Whatley. George eats spicy food. Kramer’s dental visit leads to a mix-up.
episodes.title: The Jimmy

episodes.synopsis: Jerry gets fleas in his apartment. George drapes himself in velvet. Kramer craves specific peaches. Jerry's family indulges themselves at the Plaza Hotel.
episodes.title: The Doodle

episodes.synopsis: Kramer crafts a pasta statue of Jerry. Puddy uses Jerry’s "move" on Elaine. Kramer is issued the wrong vanity license plate. Estelle gets plastic surgery.
episodes.title: The Fusilli Jerry

episodes.synopsis: Mr. Pitt thinks Elaine's trying to kill him. Jerry's act gets sidetracked by an airline pilot. Kramer wagers with a Texan at the airport.
episodes.title: The Diplomats Club

episodes.synopsis: Puddy’s hockey fandom unnerves Elaine and an unsuspecting priest. George tries to tell his girlfriend he loves her. Kramer feuds with a chimpanzee.
episodes.title: The Face Painter

episodes.synopsis: George runs over Bette Midler in a softball game. Jerry’s girlfriend cries easily. Elaine thinks her manicurists are making fun of her.
episodes.title: The Understudy

episodes.synopsis: George and Jerry lament their lack of direction in life, leading George to propose to ex-girlfriend Susan. Elaine turns to Newman to help kidnap a dog.
episodes.title: The Engagement

episodes.synopsis: George gets stressed out about his engagement. Elaine's rabbi has loose lips. Kramer spills hot coffee on himself at a movie with Jerry.
episodes.title: The Postponement

episodes.synopsis: Elaine's boyfriend insists on being called "Maestro." George gets a chair for a security guard. Kramer hires a lawyer. Jerry looks for houses in Tuscany.
episodes.title: The Maestro

episodes.synopsis: A grapefruit causes problems for George. Jerry hides his disdain for meat. Elaine dates a wake-up service caller. Kramer needs a favor from Paul O'Neill.
episodes.title: The Wink

episodes.synopsis: Jerry helps marathon runner Jean-Paul, who overslept for his last big race. George does business with Texans who swear a lot. Kramer gets a hot tub.
episodes.title: The Hot Tub

episodes.synopsis: A soup stand owner's strict ordering rules cause chaos for the gang. Jerry and his girlfriend call each other “Schmoopie.” Elaine’s armoire get stolen.
episodes.title: The Soup Nazi

episodes.synopsis: George refuses to reveal his ATM code. Jerry’s foot keeps falling asleep. Elaine dates a man who doesn’t remember meeting her. Kramer assists the FDNY.
episodes.title: The Secret Code

episodes.synopsis: Jerry’s pool guy tries to befriend him. Elaine starts hanging out with Susan, enraging George. Kramer's phone number gets confused with Moviefone.
episodes.title: The Pool Guy

episodes.synopsis: Elaine's favorite contraceptive is going off the market. Kramer joins an AIDS walk, but won't wear a ribbon. George tells Susan a secret about Jerry.
episodes.title: The Sponge

episodes.synopsis: Kramer works with Lloyd Braun to renovate a movie theater. Jerry spends too much money on Chinese gum. An old friend thinks George has a mental illness.
episodes.title: The Gum

episodes.synopsis: Frank and Estelle meet Susan's parents for the first time. Kramer feeds a horse the wrong food. Jerry shops for a marble rye. Elaine dates a saxophonist.
episodes.title: The Rye

episodes.synopsis: Steinbrenner thinks George is dead. Elaine's friend, Sue Ellen Mischke, distracts Jerry, leading to a lawsuit. Kramer seeks advice from a golf caddy.
episodes.title: The Caddy

episodes.synopsis: George wants to name a child "Seven." Elaine and Kramer enlist Newman's help to settle a dispute. Jerry dates a woman who always wears the same dress.
episodes.title: The Seven

episodes.synopsis: Jerry buys his parents a Cadillac, causing trouble in their retirement community. Kramer fights with a cable guy. George wants to date Marisa Tomei.
episodes.title: The Cadillac, Part I & II

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and George push their parents to move to Florida. Jerry’s building gets annoying, new low-flow showerheads. Elaine tests positive for opium.
episodes.title: The Shower Head

episodes.synopsis: George finds one of Susan's dolls disturbing. Elaine wants to reconcile with the Maestro. Jerry meets Sally Weaver. Frank builds a billiards room.
episodes.title: The Doll

episodes.synopsis: Jerry loses a Friars Club jacket. George wants Jerry to date Susan’s best friend. Elaine suspects a co-worker. Kramer sleeps 20 minutes at a time.
episodes.title: The Friars Club

episodes.synopsis: George and Kramer have issues with a sketchy parking lot. Jerry returns a jacket out of spite. A wig master stays with George and Susan.
episodes.title: The Wig Master

episodes.synopsis: Steinbrenner asks George to bring him a calzone every day. Elaine dates a man who never asked her out. Kramer warms up his clothes in an oven.
episodes.title: The Calzone

episodes.synopsis: Kramer and Newman hatch a bottle deposit scheme. Elaine buys famous golf clubs. A mechanic steals Jerry’s car. George is befuddled by a work assignment.
episodes.title: The Bottle Deposit, Part I & II

episodes.synopsis: Jerry and Elaine date two people who broke up over a comment by George. Kramer wears jeans that are too tight. Mickey auditions for the Actors Studio.
episodes.title: The Wait Out

episodes.synopsis: George takes a final shot at ending his engagement. Jerry falls in love with someone just like him. Kramer fights with a bank over the word "hello."
episodes.title: The Invitations

episodes.synopsis: George is asked to run a foundation in Susan's memory. Elaine takes charge of the Peterman catalog. Jerry comes to a realization about his engagement.
episodes.title: The Foundation

episodes.synopsis: George spies on a foundation board meeting with his briefcase. Kramer falls for Jerry’s girlfriend. Elaine dates a man who doesn’t want children.
episodes.title: The Soulmate

episodes.synopsis: Elaine hangs out with “bizarro” versions of Jerry, George and Kramer. Kramer pretends to have a job. Jerry’s girlfriend has “man hands.”
episodes.title: The Bizarro Jerry

episodes.synopsis: Elaine displays her embarrassing dancing skills. Jerry gets involved in bootleg filmmaking. George acts like a “bad boy” to woo Elaine’s employee.
episodes.title: The Little Kicks

episodes.synopsis: Kramer hatches a plan to get Jerry a refund on a stereo. Doctors won’t let Elaine see her medical chart. A photo store employee flirts with George.
episodes.title: The Package

episodes.synopsis: Jerry becomes Bania’s mentor. Elaine struggles with an intimidating employee. Kramer hosts a Jewish singles night. George is bothered by an audiobook.
episodes.title: The Fatigues

episodes.synopsis: Jerry gets checks for 12 cents. Kramer hosts Japanese businessmen. Elaine's boyfriend thinks Jerry is poor. George encounters a carpet cleaning cult.
episodes.title: The Checks

episodes.synopsis: A Kenny Rogers Roasters restaurant opens in the area. Elaine gets audited by Peterman for excessive spending. George tries to retrieve a Russian hat.
episodes.title: The Chicken Roaster

episodes.synopsis: Abstaining from sex has opposite effects on Elaine and George. Jerry gets bumped from career day at his high school. Kramer opens a smoking lounge.
episodes.title: The Abstinence

episodes.synopsis: George competes for an apartment with a shipwreck survivor. Kramer seeks medical care from a veterinarian. Jerry helps Newman get a transfer to Hawaii.
episodes.title: The Andrea Doria

episodes.synopsis: George dates a prison inmate. A bodega owner displays Jerry’s bounced check. Kramer buys a rooster. Elaine wants her boyfriend to grow his hair out.
episodes.title: The Little Jerry

episodes.synopsis: Jerry's parents sell the Cadillac to Jack Klompus. George's parents resolve to spend their life savings. Elaine hires Morty to work at J. Peterman.
episodes.title: The Money

episodes.synopsis: George goes to great lengths to respond to a co-worker's joke. Jerry learns his tennis pro is terrible. Elaine falls for a sensitive video store clerk.
episodes.title: The Comeback

episodes.synopsis: Kramer runs afoul of a street gang. George awards a scholarship. Elaine writes Peterman's autobiography. Jerry's girlfriend seems too perfect.
episodes.title: The Van Buren Boys

episodes.synopsis: A co-worker thinks Elaine's name is "Susie," leading to various misunderstandings. Kramer's bookie friend can’t pay up when Jerry wins bets.
episodes.title: The Susie

episodes.synopsis: George loses his keys in a pothole. Jerry drops his girlfriend's toothbrush in a toilet. Elaine gets food delivered to a closet. Kramer adopts a highway.
episodes.title: The Pothole

episodes.synopsis: Elaine hates “The English Patient.” A beautiful woman mistakes George for her boyfriend. An older man challenges Jerry to a weightlifting contest.
episodes.title: The English Patient

episodes.synopsis: Jerry gets a kitchen remodel. George takes naps under his desk. Kramer swims in the East River. Elaine has a misunderstanding about a mattress.
episodes.title: The Nap

episodes.synopsis: Tim Whatley converts to Judaism. Kramer and Mickey double date. George's girlfriend says, "yada yada" a lot. Jerry's accused of being an "anti-dentite."
episodes.title: The Yada Yada

episodes.synopsis: George tries to get fired. Elaine gets bad customer service. Kramer and Newman plan competing parties. Jerry's girlfriend moves him down her speed dial.
episodes.title: The Millennium

episodes.synopsis: George pretends to be a tourist from Arkansas. Kramer starts a "Peterman Reality Tour." Elaine helps Lippman with his muffin shop. Jerry shaves his chest.
episodes.title: The Muffin Tops

episodes.synopsis: During a summer out of work, George acts as Jerry's dating intern. Elaine’s co-worker won't swing her arms. Kramer's a seat filler at the Tony Awards.
episodes.title: The Summer of George

episodes.synopsis: George's co-workers think he has a physical disability. Kramer butters his body. Elaine and Puddy break up on a flight. Bania rides Jerry's coattails.
episodes.title: The Butter Shave

episodes.synopsis: Jerry gives his girlfriend's stomach a funny voice. Kramer hires an intern. Elaine reunites with Puddy. George refuses to leave his job.
episodes.title: The Voice

episodes.synopsis: Frank employs a new anger management strategy. George and Lloyd Braun sell computers. Elaine attends a bar mitzvah. Jerry expresses his feelings.
episodes.title: The Serenity Now

episodes.synopsis: Jerry trains with Izzy Mandelbaum. Elaine becomes a babysitter. George adds food to his sex life. Kramer stores blood at his apartment.
episodes.title: The Blood

episodes.synopsis: Kramer asks to stop getting mail. Elaine unwittingly falls for a TV pitchman. An old friend gives Jerry a van. George's parents want to see him less.
episodes.title: The Junk Mail

episodes.synopsis: Kramer starts a talk show in his apartment. George must care for a squirrel. Jerry dates a woman for her toy collection. Elaine works with a "sidler."
episodes.title: The Merv Griffin Show

episodes.synopsis: George tries to edit an incriminating photo in his boss’ office. Kramer buys a meat slicer. An alarm keeps Elaine awake. Jerry dates a dermatologist.
episodes.title: The Slicer

episodes.synopsis: Elaine, George and Jerry go to India for Sue Ellen Mischke's wedding. Kramer’s friend, FDR, makes an ominous birthday wish.
episodes.title: The Betrayal

episodes.synopsis: Jerry's girlfriend is naked all day. George clashes with a friend who's in recovery. Kramer changes his shower habits. Elaine's co-worker hates germs.
episodes.title: The Apology

episodes.synopsis: Frank brings back his holiday, "Festivus." George invents a charity. Kramer's 12-year strike at a bagel shop ends. Elaine pursues a free sandwich.
episodes.title: The Strike

episodes.synopsis: Jerry negotiates buying a car from Puddy. George can't get a Twix out of a vending machine. Kramer takes a salesman on a thrilling test drive.
episodes.title: The Dealership

episodes.synopsis: Jerry gets a bag that looks like a purse. Puddy wears a fur coat. George's wallet is stuffed too full. Newman has an affair with the super's wife.
episodes.title: The Reverse Peephole

episodes.synopsis: Sally Weaver's one-woman show about Jerry is a hit. George's girlfriend resembles Jerry. A "New Yorker" cartoon confuses Elaine. Kramer stops talking.
episodes.title: The Cartoon

episodes.synopsis: George dates two women at once. Elaine dates a poor man. Jerry fails to recognize a man who lives next door. Kramer buys a strongbox for his valuables.
episodes.title: The Strongbox

episodes.synopsis: Kramer "retires" in Florida. Jerry buys Morty a gadget. George lies about a house in the Hamptons. Elaine wonders if her boyfriend is Black.
episodes.title: The Wizard

episodes.synopsis: Kramer and Mickey act out medical scenes. Puddy tells Elaine he's religious. Jerry’s girlfriend says, "It's me." George tries to "go out on a high note."
episodes.title: The Burning

episodes.synopsis: George takes a book into a store's bathroom. Kramer and Newman start a rickshaw service. Uncle Leo shoplifts. Elaine drunkenly makes out with a co-worker.
episodes.title: The Bookstore

episodes.synopsis: George wants to preserve his high score on "Frogger." Elaine eats a vintage cake. Jerry's fear of a killer prevents him from ending a relationship.
episodes.title: The Frogger

episodes.synopsis: Jerry starts sleeping with his maid. George's boss gives him an unwanted nickname. Elaine hates her new "646" phone number. Kramer gets lost downtown.
episodes.title: The Maid

episodes.synopsis: The gang gets stuck in traffic due to the Puerto Rican Day Parade. George has a laser pointed at him. George, Jerry and Kramer crash an open house.
episodes.title: The Puerto Rican Day

episodes.synopsis: Look back at the funniest clips, most memorable quotes and unseen footage in this retrospective of the landmark series' entire run.
episodes.title: The Clip Show, Part I & II

episodes.synopsis: Jerry, George, Elaine and Kramer are arrested for violating a "good Samaritan" law, leading to a trial featuring characters from the show's past.
episodes.title: Finale, Part I & II
